<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-29T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-29T03:00:00-05:00" n="783" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/11–2948: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-29T16:00:00+08:00">November 29,
                                1948—4 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received November 29—7:22 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2356. Our best information confirms our 2355, November 29 that important
                        branches Government will move Canton and certain less important organs to
                        Chungking. No date for removal has been set.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>